.START 

Rick Faulk was named vice president, marketing for this software developer.
He will report to Frank King, senior vice president, and be responsible for overall marketing strategy.
Mr. Faulk succeeds Mark Flanagan, who resumes full-time responsibility as president of Lotus Publishing, a subsidiary.
Before coming to Lotus, Mr. Faulk founded two companies, First Software Corp., a distributor, and Creative Concepts Corp., which created and licensed software for developing personalized children's books, Lotus said. 

